  "description": "Dense sea fog: heavy damping, large splash size, very wet mix. The anchor is low — the source disappears into the atmosphere. Low undertow means no vacuum events — the fog just absorbs. Wind chaos creates vague movement within the blanket. Envelops rather than defines.",
